ygData.subject: Re: Freeport Quest Question
ygData.msgSnippet: She is very difficult to get talking.  I got her to respond but didn t write down exactly what I said.  Something like can you tell me if zimel s blades
ygData.messageBody:
She is very difficult to get talking. I got her to respond but didn't
write down exactly what I said. Something like "can you tell me if
zimel's blades existed ?" Anyhow, the next thing you ask her about if
you can ever get her to respond is "tell me about ariska zimel" or
something like that. I have made it father along the quest so it's not
broken at that point.

Shawn

-----Original Message-----
From: Jerry Phillips [mailto:cn1289@...]
Sent: Monday, May 10, 1999 1:20 PM
To: eqpaladin@onelist.com
Subject: [eqpaladin] Freeport Quest Question


From: "Jerry Phillips" <cn1289@...>

Greetings, I am a new Paladin located in the city of Freeport. I ran
across
a quest where by I would deliver a message to one of our fellow brothers
hiding undercover in the Freeport Militia. Unfortunately, he was killed
but
not before giving me a note with information about Zimel's Blades, which
I
presume is a merchant shop of some type. I returned with this info to
the
lady paladin, and she sent me to the Office of the People to speak with
Rashinda, but I seem to have hit a roadblock as I cannot get Rashinda to
reply to me. Does anyone know is this quest is working, and if so how I
might can continue it, or is the outcome not worth the trouble?

Thanks
